Raza Jaffrey https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raza_Jaffrey 0 Raza Jaffrey, (born 28 May 1975) is a British actor and singer, who starred as Dr. Neal Hudson on the CBS TV medical drama Code Black. He is best known for playing Zafar Younis on the BBC One spy drama series Spooks. In 2014, he played Pakistani Lieutenant Colonel Aasar Khan in season 4 of the Showtime series Homeland.
